    back: "Apparent authority arises where the principal represents to a third party that the agent has authority, even though actual authority is absent or exceeded. Requirements (Freeman & Lockyer v Buckhurst Park Properties [1964]): (1) representation by the principal; (2) reliance by the third party; (3) consequent alteration of position. The principal is bound.",
