    details: "Fuller used his hypothetical King Rex — who violated each requirement in turn — to illustrate how each failure undermines law's claim to be law at all. His point: there is an internal connection between law and morality, not in its substantive aims (external morality) but in its formal requirements of governance. Hart's response: these are just requirements for an efficient instrument — a Nazi law published, clear, and consistent is still law even if immoral. Fuller's contribution was to show that procedural fairness is not merely instrumental: it connects to respect for human agency (persons as rational actors who can plan their conduct). Relevance today: rule of law doctrine, Constitutional Reform Act 2005.",
